    A full online deduplication process, which
    • Retrieves duplicate clusters through OnlineDeduplication.
    • Fuses the duplicate clusters into reconciled records.

      • deduplicate

        @NonNull
public T deduplicate​(@NonNull
                     T newRecord)
        Description copied from interface: OnlineDeduplication
        Deduplicates the record with all previously seen records.

        There are two cases:

        • No duplicate has been detected: The record itself is returned.
        • At least one duplicate has been detected: The record is added to the duplicate Cluster and a suitable representation for that cluster is returned.
        Specified by:
        deduplicate in interface OnlineDeduplication<C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>>
        Parameters:
        newRecord - the record that should be processed with all previously seen records
        Returns:
        the record or a representation of the duplicate Cluster of the record.
